From f339422dc63214a7c2f4797ec29bab423014f42c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiali Chen <chenjiali@radxa.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Dec 2025 03:44:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 100/121] arm64: qcom_module.config: add qcom_module.config

Because the qcom_module_defconfig with the deconfig suffix clears the arm64/deconfig configuration [1],
causing other manufacturers' SOC to fail to start,
a symbolic link is created to qcom_module.config for use by Radxa OS,
and can also share the configuration with other BSP operating systems.

[1] https://github.com/radxa/kernel/blob/linux-6.17.1/scripts/kconfig/Makefile#L102

Signed-off-by: Jiali Chen <chenjiali@radxa.com>
---
 arch/arm64/configs/qcom_module.config | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
 create mode 120000 arch/arm64/configs/qcom_module.config

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_module.config b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_module.config
new file mode 120000
index 000000000000..975c6c938e39
--- /dev/null
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/qcom_module.config
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+./qcom_module_defconfig
\ No newline at end of file
-- 
2.39.5

